<br>
Something that you said stuck in my head, and I want to explain something to you further.  You wanted to know why we get so worked up about these things.  Why we take our reputation so seriously.  This post will be my attempt to explain why without flaming, just so that you can see what you are up against.<br>
<br>
I've been on this server since the day 1.  No, I don't want a medal, I'm not trying to give my &quot;FV street creds&quot;, just trying to give a time line.  Anyway, in that time, I've made upwards of 20-25 characters here.  All of them evil.  And all of them in Prime Nightmare.  Am I crazy? Probably.  But I could not ask for a better home.<br>
<br>
This guild, as I mentioned in the other thread, stands for something.  An idea, maybe. A place that is as true to the vision as we can make it.  An army of evils, and only evils, that do evil stuff.  When FV started this wasn't all that uncommon.  Now it is, and we stand with very few guilds now that remain that way.<br>
<br>
When you start talking out your ass about how we &quot;Sold out&quot;, so to speak, it pisses us off.  Do you know why?<br>
<br>
Because it is fucking hard to be evil.  To only group with evils.  To only roleplay evil.  Most of our guild, at some point or another, have had problems finding groups.  That is because we have such a small pool of available people who are:<br>
<br>
1.&gt; Evilly aligned, and<br>
2.&gt; Agree to only group with other evils, and <br>
3.&gt; Want to continue being this way for the life of their <br>
character, and<br>
4.&gt; Are willing to Roleplay.<br>
<br>
You've seen our charter.  Take a look at it again, and realize just how limited our members are for character advancement.  To be honest, it sucks.  <br>
<br>
Examples?  How about like getting to a small raid and having to leave because one of the clerics is a Dorf.  Or having one camp that you need to finish a quest, and having a group of 5 lighties there as well that want you to join them, and leaving.  Refusing a res from a halfling, when you know you will have to eat the exp loss as there are no evil clerics (only 3 possible race/class combos) on.  And so on.<br>
<br>
These kind of situations, frankly, suck from a gameplay standpoint.  So why do we do it?<br>
<br>
Because that is what we think is best for us, our characters, and the RP health of FV in general.  Not because we want to be &quot;elitest&quot;, not because of phat lewt (har har), but because we want to.   It's the road less travelled, not the path of least resistance.  <br>
<br>
And I reiterate, it is difficult.  But these are all choices that I and all of those in PN have made, trying  keep the spirit of FV alive.  Prime Nightmare stands proud of what we are, and any half-witted atatck on our values is a slap in the face to all of those frustrating moments that we have all felt staying true to the alignemnts.<br>
<br>
To let you get away with your slander isn't even an option, we've given up too much to have the reputation that we have.  That is why you will be flamed each and every time you go on one of your bizarre crusades.  We work hard for what we have, and don't want you pissing in our collective, figurative Cheerios (R)<br>
<br>
This is fair warning.  I hope you better understand now.<br>
<br>
