Squishy, did it ever occur to you that you have so many problems with so many people because of YOU and not them? <br>
<br>
For a while there, I thought you were cool. I even felt really terrible for you during that whole Harmony/Pixxie thing... to the point that when I saw Harmony, I thought oh its Harmony, that asshole... <br>
<br>
And after reading so many posts where YOU are the victim of so many people... I started to notice a trend. You stir the shit, and cant handle the backsplash. And when people call you on it, you get all high and mighty trying to present yourself as the innocent one. <br>
<br>
That made me realize probably there was a whole lot more behind Pixxie/Harmony than was let on, and you did it to promote your oh so fitting FV board tittle of Drama Queen. And now I actually feel bad for being mad at Harmony, and falling into your sticky web of bullshit.<br>
<br>
Flaunting the fact that you are on medication, as an excuse for your behavior, is not only sad, but destructive. The fucking point of being on medication is to get better... not to have an excuse for your outbursts and tantrums. You defending yourself with medication makes other people who maybe are considering going on it, think WTF I don't want to act like her, so I'll continue being miserable. That is just wrong.<br>
<br>
Maybe its time for you to step back and take a look at yourself, see if you can find your flaws and either fix them or accept them... rather than trying to project them onto every other living soul. It will save you a great deal of heartbreak and pain.<br>
<br>
